albums.title: Mindsets

songs.title: Wanderers
songs.about: Wanderers (Sep 10 2020Nov 26 2020) was the last song i started for the album. i was finally getting satisfied with the set of songs i had, but i then had the challenge of putting it all together to somehow make an album. i felt very lost from september all the way to january, when the (pretty much) final version of the album was finished. but i made it!!!

songs.title: Looking Forward
songs.about: Looking Forward (Mar 18 2020Apr 19 2020) was the first song i made for Mindsets, and it's all about the joy of having so many possibilities in front of you and being excited to try it all. it first debuted on SPACEAGE RADIO ep. 4 back in may 2020, and, true to a promise i made to myself, i haven't changed it at all since i sent it in april.

songs.title: Good Person
songs.about: Good Person (Aug 16 2020Jan 9 2021) is about my fear of failure, as both a producer and as a good person in general. oh, and if you couldn't tell, it was based on the same project file as Go Go Go Go (from 10k Degrees).

songs.title: One Day
songs.about: One Day (Jun 24 2020Jan 9 2021) is like a continuation of the previous song, in that i always look up towards what i want to make, but i never feel like i'll make the leap from where i am now to there. this sorta coincides with the anxiety of releasing music, Mindsets especially, because there will always be a gap between my first vision and where i ended up.

songs.title: Better
songs.about: Better (Jun 9 2020Nov 27 2020), as its one vocal line indicates, is about frustration with everything i make and the longing for improvement which always seems so far away.

songs.title: Identity
songs.about: Identity (May 14 2020Jan 10 2021) has been through a lot as a song. it has some scrapped lyrics that are sorta me talking my way through my thoughts of how i present myself. it boils down to the fact that, at times, i feel disconnected from "Astro", the name i've associated with myself for 7 years now.

songs.title: Hour Twenty-Four
songs.about: Hour Twenty-Four (May 8 2020Jan 24 2021) is really just about stress and stuff lol. all these other songs are about complicated emotions and creative struggle, but this one is just about me being worried all the time.

songs.title: Stargazing
songs.about: Hour Twenty-Four (May 8 2020Jan 24 2021) is really just about stress and stuff lol. all these other songs are about complicated emotions and creative struggle, but this one is just about me being worried all the time.

songs.title: Mandatory Good Vibes
songs.about: Mandatory Good Vibes (Jul 17 2020Nov 20 2020) was made mostly in the span of two days, during which i felt very optimistic for some reason. or, as i put it in my project file notes, "shut up! shut up! lets be happy". the first name of its project file was "just started writing.mmpz" because i did just that: most of it came to me all at once.

songs.title: Holocene
songs.about: Holocene (Aug 22 2020Nov 27 2020), much like Mandatory Good Vibes, is about a super instantaneous joy i felt during its conception. these two songs are both super happy-sounding and i love how fun it is to listen to them.

songs.title: Out in the Open (feat. bandanabloom)
songs.about: Out in the Open (feat. bandanabloom) (Apr 25 2020Mar 21 2021) is absolutely my favorite song from this entire album. it's about my worries about friends who've stopped talking to me. i worry about whether or not i've upset them, if i'm annoying, things like that. i'm just hoping that, one day, they'll come back and maybe we'll talk again. featuring bandanabloom on this was actually a last-minute decision, but i'm so glad we did it because i love these lyrics and the song is packed with so many emotions.

songs.title: Together Again
songs.about: Together Again (Aug 16 2020Dec 2 2020), leading out of the previous song, is a continuation of sorts. i wrote it right after talking to an old friend for the first time in a while, and it felt so surreal to speak with them again, so i wanted to put that happiness into sounds.

songs.title: Thank You
songs.about: Thank You (Apr 22 2020Dec 2 2020) was made late at night (well, i guess most of these songs were) and i wanted to capture the overwhelming gratitude i felt for all my friends and listeners who've stayed with me for so long. at times it really feels like i'm failing, and i haven't really grown significantly for a long time, but everyone who continues to listen to everything i put out means so much to me.

songs.title: Best Part (feat. bandanabloom)
songs.about: Best Part (feat. bandanabloom) (Jun 12 2020Jan 10 2021) is such a beautiful song and i had so much fun making it!! this song is all about the comforting feeling i get from listening to music and being sincere about that. even just listening to this single makes me so excited for the album to come out!

albums.about: Mindsets is the set of songs I've been working on since March of 2020, even through 10k Degrees. This is the longest I've spent working on a single project, and I'm so excited for you all to hear this!

albums.about: somewhere in the milky way is an album inspired by the soundtracks of some of my favorite games (namely Animal Crossing: City Folk and Minecraft). Each song is thematically written around an hour of the day, starting at 6 a.m. The album is divided into four discs: the morning disc, the afternoon disc, the evening disc, and the night disc. Altogether two hours of chill vibes. A digital download will also include alternate "snowdrift" versions of each song for wintertime listening.

albums.about:
Mint Gum is a mix of songs I've been working on over the past two years that don't really have a home on any of the more conceptual albums I've been working on. I'm naturally hesitant to share details (I like to be surprising!) but, during 2023, I really got in my own head about releasing music altogether. I kept looking back at past albums with fascination and admiration, as if someone else entirely had put them together. I spent the entire year working on and obsessing over my next album album, wanting so badly to make the best set of songs imaginable. Of course, that obsession and self-imposed pressure can be both helpful and unhelpful.

Those songs are probably still on their way, but as I bide my time, I put together this lighthearted collection of songs that have been loitering on my hard drive for too long! Some of them are outtakes from that 2023 album ("unicorn", "ok girl !", "Endless V", "bitter taste", and "Handsome"), a few were tossed around as collaborations between Rey and I before we chose "ROSALIE" ("Andromeda Galaxy", "Hydrogen", and "Bzier Curve"), and the rest are songs made for specific events, and album concepts that went nowhere. And "winter nights : sweet dreams" was the first song I made for somewhere in the milky way! Wow!

albums.title: Absolute Zero

songs.title: Are You Ready to Go to Space? (Demo)

albums.about:
Taking this out of the 2021 archives!

This was a companion album to Exosphere, my first exploration of ambient-adjacent music. In Absolute Zero, I wanted to tap back into those sparse soundscapes from Exosphere, while still being distinctly electronica. Over the summer of 2021, when Absolute Zero was done and its scheduled September release was right around the corner, I learned a lot more about production, collaborated a lot more with my close friends, and fell out of love with Absolute Zero. By September, all I wanted to do was focus on f(x) so I could finish that by December. In some sense, I don't "stand by" the music from Absolute Zero anymore. Had I made this in the current year, I wouldn't have released it. But this music holds a special place in my heart!

My good friend Nadia is the only person who's been aware of Absolute Zero, I think. I sent it to her long before the planned 2021 release because she liked using Exosphere in video essays. She also later commissioned a rendition of Schubert's "Ave Maria", which became track 13, "Varda".

albums.title: OBSESSED
albums.about: I released an obscene number of remixes during 2023 and 2024. I am heavily influenced by the online plunderphonic and hyperflip scenes. High-energy electronic music has always been my escape. OBSESSED is a snapshot of my life two years ago that indulges in the connection between sample-based dance music and feelings of despair and addiction. As I pieced it together, it dawned on me that this is the kind of music I needed to make. I hope the music does its job of communicating that exact set of feelings, and I also don't really care if it doesn't. First person to identify all 100 samples on this album gets $20.

albums.title: Staring Straight at the Sun
albums.about:
Staring Straight at the Sun is a set of pop vocal songs I've been working on for a little over three years. Originally slated for a summer 2023 release, this project consumed my life, and I'm glad it did. I promised myself I wouldn't release this album until I was the one singing on it: no copping out by releasing instrumentals or entirely depending on featured vocalists.

In making this project, I've learned a lot about lyrical songwriting and producing with vocals. I've been paying more attention to restraint and focus in my sound design. Staring Straight at the Sun constitutes my sincere attempt at making pop music; I'm excited to do it all over again.
